            Identify and prevent unauthorized modifications to AI models and their runtime environments.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-4 text-mid-gray">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Detect malicious libraries or resources loaded at runtime</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Monitor for suspicious network connections or data exfiltration</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Create tamper-evident cryptographic records of AI operations</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Use Case 2 (formerly Use Case 3) -->
      <div class="use-case-row flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center">
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 mb-8 md:mb-0">
          <div class="use-case-number text-8xl font-bold text-primary/30">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Critical Infrastructure Protection</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 pl-0 md:pl-12 slide-in-right">
          <p class="mb-6 text-lg text-mid-gray">
            Actively protect AI systems in mission-critical environments with a trust-based security model that prevents unauthorized access.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg mb-6 border border-gray-200">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Airport Security AI Example</h4>
            <p class="mb-4 text-mid-gray">
              Modern airports rely on AI systems for passenger screening and threat detection. Bomfather secures these systems by:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-mid-gray pl-5 list-disc">
              <li>Creating a whitelist of trusted components (screening algorithms, model weights, reference databases)</li>
              <li>Blocking any attempt to load unauthorized code or backdoors at runtime</li>
              <li>Preventing attackers from extracting sensitive passenger data through unauthorized channels</li>
              <li>Generating cryptographic proof of proper system operation for security audits</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-4 text-mid-gray">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Define trusted files for critical AI systems and <strong>automatically block all other accesses</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Prevent data exfiltration with real-time blocking of unauthorized network connections</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent-green mt-1 mr-3 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span>Maintain operational continuity while blocking threatsâ€”safer than trying to identify every possible malicious file</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .slide-in-right {
    /* We'll now handle the initial state via JavaScript to avoid conflicts */
    visibility: hidden; /* Hide initially but keep layout intact */
  }
  
  .use-case-number {
    line-height: 1;
  }
</style>

<script>
  import { gsap } from 'gsap';
  import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';
  
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    // Register ScrollTrigger with GSAP
    gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
    
    // Initial header animation
    gsap.from('.gsap-reveal', {
      opacity: 0,
      y: 30,
      stagger: 0.2,
      duration: 1,
      ease: 'power2.out'
    });
    
    // Set up animations for use case rows
    const useCaseRows = document.querySelectorAll('.use-case-row');
    
    useCaseRows.forEach((row) => {
      const slideInElement = row.querySelector('.slide-in-right');
      const numberElement = row.querySelector('.use-case-number');
      
      // Set initial state of the elements (make them visible for GSAP)
      gsap.set(slideInElement, { 
        visibility: 'visible',
        opacity: 0,
        x: 50
      });
      
      // Create the timeline with markers for debugging
      const tl = gsap.timeline({
        scrollTrigger: {
          trigger: row,
          start: 'top 80%',  // Trigger when the top of the row hits 80% down the viewport
          end: 'bottom 20%', // End when the bottom of the row is 20% from the top of the viewport
          toggleActions: 'play none none none', // Only play forward, don't reset
          once: false,        // Can play multiple times
          // markers: true    // Uncomment for debugging
        }
      });
      
      // Add animations to the timeline
      tl.from(numberElement, {
        opacity: 0,
        x: -30,
        duration: 0.8,
        ease: 'power2.out'
      });
      
      tl.to(slideInElement, {
        opacity: 1,
        x: 0,
        duration: 0.8,
        ease: 'power2.out'
      }, '-=0.4');
    });
  });
</script> 